File: MTN branding seen at an event. BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu JOHANNESBURG - Mobile giant MTN's share price is up 8 percent following a good showing for the first three months of the year. Continued strong demand for data by work-from-home users saw mobile data revenue growing by 18.5 percent. READ: MTN slashes data prices But MTN lost five million subscribers in Nigeria due to new registration regulations in the country. For South Africa, total subscribers increased around 95,000 in the quarter to just more than 32 million.